sql:
SELECT topic_name, start_date, end_date, popularity_score, platform, trend_rank, source 
FROM trending_topics 
WHERE topic_name = 'Gun Laws';

external_knowledge:
- "political virtuosos" refers to political figures; 
- "eloquent wisdom" and "seeds of their sentiments" metaphorically describe the content and sentiment of the tweets;
- "domains of discourse" refers to the categories of content the tweets belong to;
- "blossoms of their most effusive expressions" represents the highest sentiment scores of the tweets.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT user_id)
FROM scheduling
WHERE post_time > datetime('now');

external_knowledge:
- "flowers of discourse" refers to tweets; 
- "fragrances" metaphorically represents sentiment scores; 
- "soil of Californian Republican politics" refers to political figures who are Republicans from California; 
- "fertilized by over a thousand admirers" means the tweets come from accounts with more than 1000 followers; 
- "seeds are planted in the soil labeled 'Gun Laws'" indicates the category of the tweets.

sql:
SELECT tweets.text, tweets.favorites
FROM tweets
WHERE tweets.favorites > (SELECT AVG(favorites) FROM tweets);
